provApp.admin.actionGetXMLConf(modeladmin, request, queryset)¶

This function is used as admin action on lisf of devices. Parameters are automatic: modeladmin, request, queryset. The data is shown in same window and therefore to continue with administration it is necessary to click back button.

provApp.admin.turnOffFields(form, fields)¶

This function receives a form and list of fields which are foreign key shown on same form, and then disables edit or add values over forign key

provApp.endpoints module¶

provApp.endpoints.GetXMLConfig(device_id)¶

Function that, based on device id, collect XML configuration for a device. In same time the function updates cfg_last_update time for the requested device.

provApp.serializers module¶

This functionality of serializers is available:

CRUD tested with postman C ADD A RECORD: method POST; http://localhost:8000/api/devvendor/ form-data - name = “Value”

R GET ALL RECORDS: method GET; http://localhost:8000/api/devvendor/ GET SPECIFIC RECORD: method GET; http://localhost:8000/api/devvendor/10/

U UPDATE A RECORD: method PUT; http://localhost:8000/api/devvendor/13/ form-data - name = “Value”

UPDATE A RECORD WITHOUT PROVIDING ALL THE REQUIRED FIELDS: method PATCH; http://localhost:8000/api/extension/11/ form-data - name = “new value”

D DELETE A RECORD: method DELETE; http://localhost:8000/api/devvendor/13/

provApp.tests module¶

provApp.urls module¶

Define URL for application provApp. On the project side all of the URLs define here are under /API/.

URLs here are for REST API: ‘/api/devvendor/’ -> DevVendorViewSet ‘/api/devmodel/’ -> DevModelViewSet ‘/api/device/’ -> DeviceViewSet ‘/api/customer/’ -> CustomerViewSet ‘/api/extension/’ -> ExtensionViewSet ‘/api/dss/’ -> DSSViewSet ‘/api/xml/’ -> GetXMLConfigEndpoint
